Package: microvars
Title: Tools for Exploratory Microbiome Analysis by Metadata Variables
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("First", "Last", , "first.last@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: microvars simplifies the exploratory analysis of microbiome data by 
  leveraging metadata variables. Built on top of the phyloseq framework, it 
    offers user-friendly functions for performing statistical tests and generating 
    customizable visualizations. This package is designed to accelerate the 
    initial exploration and interpretation of microbiome datasets, making it 
    easier to uncover patterns and associations linked to sample metadata such 
    as sex, location, or treatment.
License: `use_mit_license()`, `use_gpl3_license()` or friends to pick a
    license
